fields.description:
/etc/security/limits.conf

The bamboo user should have more than the default 1024.  One example fix would be to add the possible lines.  
{noformat}
bamboo        soft    nofile  8096
bamboo        hard    nofile  8096
{noformat}

Custom setup on MySQL 5.1, this happens before data import. 
{code}
2011-02-14 13:04:01,625 ERROR [performSetupDatabaseConnectionBackgroundThread] [SchemaExport] Unsuccessful: create index label_name_namespace_index on LABEL (NAME, NAMESPACE)
2011-02-14 13:04:01,625 ERROR [performSetupDatabaseConnectionBackgroundThread] [SchemaExport] Specified key was too long; max key length is 1000 bytes
{code}

This could potentially cause some performance problems.

Currently, a Maven build being run with the following Goal:
{code}
-B release:prepare release:perform -DperformRelease=true
{code}
will not be able to commit to SVN using the credentials provided at the Repository tab.

It demands the definition of:
{code}
-Dusername=usr -Dpassword=pwd
{code}

Would be easier if both the Repository and Builder tabs could share the password.
